67943","viewerDidAuthor":false}],"reviews":[{"id":"PRR_kwDOSjZ7L88AAAABA4Bxxw","author":{"login":"codefactor-io"},"authorAssociation":"NONE","body":"","submittedAt":"2026-05-25T00:57:26Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"reactionGroups":[],"state":"COMMENTED","commit":{"oid":"36d79f0553139334b7d234792d83ac8b0a369a0d"}},{"id":"PRR_kwDOSjZ7L88AAAABA4Bz-g","author":{"login":"amazon-q-developer"},"authorAssociation":"NONE","body":"The circuit breaker race condition fixes are correctly implemented. The addition of `ref` keywords for `syncPending` and `reservedDelta` parameters ensures atomic state updates during rollback, and the unconditional state resets prevent partial rollback scenarios. All call sites are properly updated and the implementation aligns with V12 DNA principles for lock-free operations.\n\n---\nYou can now have the agent implement changes and create commits directly on your pull request's source branch. Simply comment with /q followed by your request in natural language to ask the agent to make changes.\n","submittedAt":"2026-05-25T00:57:44Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"reactionGroups":[],"state":"COMMENTED","commit":{"oid":"36d79f0553139334b7d234792d83ac8b0a369a0d"}},{"id":"PRR_kwDOSjZ7L88AAAABA4B1qw","author":{"login":"sourcery-ai"},"authorAssociation":"NONE","body":"Hey - I've found 1 issue, and left some high level feedback:\n\n- Now that `RollbackCircuitBreakerState` takes `ref` parameters and mutates `syncPending`/`reservedDelta`, consider updating the methodГ”ГҮГ–s XML doc or name to clearly document these side effects so future callers donГ”ГҮГ–t accidentally reuse stale values.\n- Since `RollbackCircuitBreakerState`Г”ГҮГ–s signature changed to use `ref`, it may be worth quickly verifying there are no remaining call sites using the old value semantics (e.g., via a search for `RollbackCircuitBreakerState(`) to avoid silent mismatches.\n\n<details>\n<summary>Prompt for AI Agents</summary>\n\n~~~markdown\nPlease address the comments from this code review:\n\n## Overall Comments\n- Now that `RollbackCircuitBreakerState` takes `ref` parameters and mutates `syncPending`/`reservedDelta`, consider updating the methodГ”ГҮГ–s XML doc or name to clearly document these side effects so future callers donГ”ГҮГ–t accidentally reuse stale values.\n- Since `RollbackCircuitBreakerState`Г”ГҮГ–s signature changed to use `ref`, it may be worth quickly verifying there are no remaining call sites using the old value semantics (e.g., via a search for `RollbackCircuitBreakerState(`) to avoid silent mismatches.\n\n## Individual Comments\n\n### Comment 1\n<location path=\"src/V12_002.SIMA.Dispatch.cs\" line_range=\"1099-1108\" />\n<code_context>\n             string fleetEntryName\n         )\n         {\n+            // Unconditional state resets (P0 race condition fix)\n             if (syncPending)\n+            {\n                 ClearDispatchSyncPending(expectedKey);\n+                syncPending = false;\n+            }\n             if (reservedDelta != 0)\n+            {\n                 AddExpectedPositionDeltaLocked(expectedKey, -reservedDelta);\n+                reservedDelta = 0;\n+            }\n             if (poolSlotIndex >= 0)\n</code_context>\n<issue_to_address>\n**nitpick:** The comment about \"unconditional\" resets conflicts with the conditional checks that follow.\n\nThe code still conditionally clears state (`if (syncPending)`, `if (reservedDelta != 0)`), so calling these Г”ГҮВЈUnconditional state resetsГ”ГҮГҳ is misleading. Please rephrase to indicate these are resets applied when the corresponding flags/values are set (e.g., Г”ГҮВЈEnsure any pending sync and reserved delta are cleared if presentГ”ГҮГҳ) to better reflect the actual behavior and avoid future confusion.\n</issue_to_address>\n~~~\n\n</details>\n\n***\n\n<details>\n<summary>Sourcery is free for open source - if you like our reviews please consider sharing them Г”ВЈВҝ</summary>\n\n- [X](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=I%20just%20got%20an%20