8b0a369a0d"}},{"id":"PRR_kwDOSjZ7L88AAAABA4B_8w","author":{"login":"greptile-apps"},"authorAssociation":"NONE","body":"","submittedAt":"2026-05-25T00:59:48Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"reactionGroups":[],"state":"COMMENTED","commit":{"oid":"36d79f0553139334b7d234792d83ac8b0a369a0d"}},{"id":"PRR_kwDOSjZ7L88AAAABA4CGPQ","author":{"login":"codacy-production"},"authorAssociation":"NONE","body":"### Pull Request Overview\n\nWhile this PR introduces the 'ref' keyword to the rollback helper, it contains a critical architectural mismatch: the outer 'TryIncrementDispatchCountWithCircuitBreaker' method still receives 'syncPending' and 'reservedDelta' by value. This means the state resets intended to fix the P0 race conditions will only affect local copies and will not reach the primary caller. \n\nFurthermore, 'poolSlotIndex' is at risk of being double-released because it is not incorporated into the idempotent reset pattern. Although Codacy rates the PR as 'Up to Standards', the method 'TryIncrementDispatchCountWithCircuitBreaker' exceeds the complexity/length threshold due to duplicated logic paths. These issues, combined with a lack of unit tests for the fix, should prevent merging until the signature mismatch is resolved.\n\n#### About this PR\n- The state synchronization logic is currently incomplete. Ensuring variables are reset in a helper method is insufficient if the intermediate wrapper method still passes those variables by value. This pattern must be applied consistently from the top-most caller down to the rollback logic to ensure the system state remains consistent after a circuit breaker trip.\n\n<details>\n<summary><b><code>2</code> comments outside of the diff</b></summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary><code>src/V12_002.SIMA.Dispatch.cs</code></summary>\n\n> <sub>`line 1028` :white_circle: LOW RISK</sub>\n> Suggestion: The method length (55 lines) exceeds the 50-line limit. Consolidate the two 'if' blocks (the threshold check and the 'already tripped' check) into a single conditional block to reduce duplication and improve maintainability.\n\n> <sub>`line 1028` :white_circle: LOW RISK</sub>\n> Suggestion: The method length (55 lines) exceeds the 50-line limit. The logic for handling the circuit breaker can be simplified by merging the threshold check and the 'already tripped' check into a single conditional block.\n\n</details>\n\n</details>\n\n#### Test suggestions\n- [ ] Verify that syncPending is reset to false in the caller's scope after RollbackCircuitBreakerState execution.\n- [ ] Verify that reservedDelta is reset to 0 in the caller's scope after RollbackCircuitBreakerState execution.\n- [ ] Verify that ClearDispatchSyncPending is called when syncPending is true during a circuit breaker trip.\n- [ ] Verify that reserved position deltas are correctly reversed via AddExpectedPositionDeltaLocked during rollback.\n\n<details>\n<summary>Prompt proposal for missing tests</summary>\n\n```\nConsider implementing these tests if applicable:\n1. Verify that syncPending is reset to false in the caller's scope after RollbackCircuitBreakerState execution.\n2. Verify that reservedDelta is reset to 0 in the caller's scope after RollbackCircuitBreakerState execution.\n3. Verify that ClearDispatchSyncPending is called when syncPending is true during a circuit breaker trip.\n4. Verify that reserved position deltas are correctly reversed via AddExpectedPositionDeltaLocked during rollback.\n```\n\n</details>\n\n\n\n##\n\n<sub>`TIP` Improve review quality by [adding custom instructions](https://docs.codacy.com/codacy-ai/codacy-ai/#custom-instructions)</sub>\n<sub>`TIP` How was this review? [Give us feedback](https://tally.so/r/jaBlA1?org=mdasdispatch-hash&repo=universal-or-strategy&pr=10)</sub>\n<!-- e34d5167-b092-49eb-b8c8-33859ab00079 -->","submittedAt":"2026-05-25T01:00:51Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"reactionGroups":[],"state":"COMMENTED","commit":{"oid":"36d79f0553139334b7d234792d83ac8b0a369a0d"}},{"id":"PRR_kwDOSjZ7L88AAAABA4NpoA"